Subject: [Read_Alphabet] Re: what's the differences between Shavian and Read

side comparision at
http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Read_Alphabet/files/gp/readscripts.gif

--- satnordameriko wrote:

> > and what were the problems with
Shavian?

--- page wrote:
> QS is simplified a little from
Shavian. 
> An example is that he deleted the accented schwa
symbol.

SB:  The initial vowel in <up> and <ago> are written the same way.

> PG: Quikscript is strongly cursive although
letters are attached
> only when one letter naturally leads into another

>  Shavian letters, on the other hand, are not connected.
